{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"17729771-e3fd-4b1d-b189-fc80e0f98119","content":"## JDK Version Mismatch\n\n**The problem:** .NET MAUI for .NET 9+ requires **JDK 21**. You have JDK 17, which is too old.\n\nStarting with .NET 9, the Android build tooling (r35 Android SDK Build-Tools / AGP upgrades) bumped the minimum to JDK 21. JDK 17 was only valid for .NET 8 MAUI.\n\n## Fix\n\nInstall the Microsoft OpenJDK 21 (recommended for MAUI) or Adoptium Temurin 21:\n\n```bash\n# Option A – Microsoft OpenJDK 21 (recommended)\nbrew install --cask microsoft-openjdk@21\n\n# Option B – Adoptium Temurin 21\nbrew install --cask temurin@21\n```\n\nThen update `JAVA_HOME`:\n\n```bash\n# For Microsoft OpenJDK 21:\nexport JAVA_HOME=\"/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/microsoft-21.jdk/Contents/Home\"\n\n# For Temurin 21:\nexport JAVA_HOME=\"/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/temurin-21.jdk/Contents/Home\"\n```\n\nAdd the appropriate line to your `~/.zshrc` (or `~/.bash_profile`) to persist it.\n\nYou can also set it per-project in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <JavaSdkDirectory>$(JAVA_HOME)</JavaSdkDirectory>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nAfter updating, verify with `java -version` showing **21.x**, then rebuild.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e30ccdfc-17e2-4205-94f5-22021e016fe6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is having a .NET MAUI Android build failure with a Java-related error on macOS. They have Adoptium Temurin JDK 17.0.12 installed with JAVA_HOME pointing to it.\n\nLet me think about what's likely going on here. .NET MAUI Android builds require a specific version of JDK. Let me check what the common issues are:\n\n1. .NET MAUI / Xamarin Android has specific JDK version requirements\n2. As of .NET 8+, MAUI requires JDK 17\n3. But there's a known issue: on macOS, the JAVA_HOME path for Adoptium Temurin JDK needs to point to the correct location\n\n\n4. The build system might be using the bundled Microsoft OpenJDK instead of respecting the JAVA_HOME environment variable, or there could be a path configuration issue specific to how Temurin is installed on macOS\n\n.\n\nActually, the version requirement is the more likely culprit here. .NET 8 MAUI needs JDK 17, but .NET 9 MAUI bumped that requirement up to JDK 21. If the user is running .NET 9 with only JDK 17 installed, that version mismatch would definitely cause build failures.","outputTokens":1102,"requestId":"B7D6:3611D2:12B8B4:188D38:69FFD7AC"},"id":"b6dc8273-5dbd-4c29-81dc-89547c380a46","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:56:33.577Z","parentId":"3bb51ed9-2ca7-4e5b-afa9-eb0219e9ed16"}
